Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), dh-sequence-python3, gdb <!nocheck>, help2man, python3-all-dbg, python3-all-dev, python3-numpy <!nocheck>, python3-setuptools <!nocheck>, python3-sphinx
Description: C-Extensions for Python 3 Cython is a language that makes writing C extensions for the Python language as easy as Python itself. Cython is based on the well-known Pyrex, but supports more cutting edge functionality and optimizations. . The Cython language is very close to the Python language, but Cython additionally supports calling C functions and declaring C types on variables and class attributes. This allows the compiler to generate very efficient C code from Cython code. . This makes Cython the ideal language for wrapping external C libraries, and for fast C modules that speed up the execution of Python code.
Package-List: cython-doc deb doc optional arch=all cython3 deb python optional arch=any
Testsuite-Triggers: g++, gcc, gdb, make, python3-all, python3-all-dev, python3-numpy, python3-setuptools
